GameStrings.UI/HelpGameMechanic_BruiserMinions_Descr:
• [ph]Super strong minions
  • [ph]Spawns in the lane where the fortification closest to the Palace is destroyed.
GameStrings.UI/HelpGameMechanic_Bushes_Description:
• These sight blockers hide whatever is in and behind them from heroes on the ground.
  • Heroes on the ground must stand inside or walk through sight blockers to see what is on the other side.
  • Flying heroes are not affected and can act as spotters to see into or through sight blockers.
GameStrings.UI/HelpGameMechanic_Experience_Descripti:
• Experience is earned when a teammate is close to an enemy minion when it dies, when an enemy hero dies, or when an enemy fortification is destroyed.
  • Experience earned is shared across the team.
  • Leveling up gives you talents and better hero stats.
GameStrings.UI/HelpGameMechanic_FogofWar_Description: • Fog of War limits a team's vision to what its members and minions can see.
GameStrings.UI/HelpGameMechanic_Gates_Description:
• Allies can pass through but enemies cannot.
  • Attack gates to destroy them.
GameStrings.UI/HelpGameMechanic_HealthGlobes_Descrip:
• These globes drop off some enemy minions when they are killed.
  • Walk over them to gain health and mana.
  • Each hero gains the full amount of the health globe when it is collected.
GameStrings.UI/HelpGameMechanic_MercenaryCamps_Descr: • [ph]Defeat these camps and they will fight for you or drop map mechanic stuff
GameStrings.UI/HelpGameMechanic_Moonwells_Descriptio:
• Right-click a friendly moonwell to regain health and mana.
  • [ph]Wait to use it again.
GameStrings.UI/HelpGameMechanic_TowerAmmunition_Desc:
• Towers always target minions first and then heroes.
  • Some towers have limited ammunition and will stop firing when the ammunition is used up.
  • Ammunition replenishes itself over time.
GameStrings.UI/HelpGameMechanic_VisionTowers_Descrip:
• These towers provide a large sight radius when secured by a hero
  • If an enemy hero approaches, the tower becomes contested and will not provide vision until it is under a single team's control again.

GameStrings.UI/VideoOptionsTooltips/AudioQuality: <c val="ffffff">Audio Quality:</c><n/>Increasing audio quality will provide greater audio fidelity at a cost of larger video files.
GameStrings.UI/VideoOptionsTooltips/FrameRate: <c val="ffffff">Framerate:</c><n/>Framerate refers to the number of frames recorded per second. GameStrings.UI/VideoOptionsTooltips/RecordTriggers: <c val="ffffff">Record From Triggers:</c><n/>Enabling this option will allow you to record video from in-game triggers. GameStrings.UI/VideoOptionsTooltips/Resolution: <c val="ffffff">Resolution:</c><n/>Determines the size in pixels of the recorded video. Higher resolutions have much better image quality, but they are slower to record. For best results, use a resolution that matches your game's aspect ratio.
GameStrings.UI/VideoOptionsTooltips/SlowGame: <c val="ffffff">Slow Game while Recording:</c><n/>Determines whether or not game time will slow down to adjust for the performance drop while recording video. This will result in better looking videos, but it cannot be used while participating in multiplayer games. Videos recorded with this option disabled will record the drop in framerate, but your audio will be unaffected.
GameStrings.UI/VideoOptionsTooltips/VideoQuality: <c val="ffffff">Video Quality:</c><n/>Determines the amount of compression used when recording your video. Greater video quality will result in better image quality but much larger video files.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/AGC: <c val="ffffff">Microphone Automatic Gain Control:</c><n/>Toggles automatic gain control for the microphone, which will adjust the outgoing sound levels to maintain a constant volume.<n/><n/><c val="ff0000">Note: This will change the operating system settings for the microphone. GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/ActivatedSensiti: <c val="ffffff">Microphone Activation Sensitivity:</c><n/>Determines how loudly you must speak before voice chat is activated. Keep this lower if breathing and other incidental sounds are triggering voice chat.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/ChatVolume: <c val="ffffff">Voice Chat Output Volume:</c><n/>Determines how loudly voice chat plays back.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/FadeMusicVolume: <c val="ffffff">Fade Music Level:</c><n/>This determines the level that music should play while someone is speaking.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/FadeSoundVolume: <c val="ffffff">Fade Sound Level:</c><n/>This determines the level that game sounds should play while someone is speaking. Use this if you are having trouble hearing other people over gameplay or if your game sounds are recorded while speaking.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/InputDevice: <c val="ffffff">Input Device:</c><n/>Selects the microphone or headset used for voice chat.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/Microphone: <c val="ffffff">Enable Talking:</c><n/>Enables the ability to participate in voice chat during gameplay. You must have an input device such as a microphone, headset, or built-in microphone.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/MicrophoneBoost: <c val="ffffff">Microphone Boost:</c><n/>Increases the power of a traditional microphone. This may cause distortion with USB headsets or microphones. Not all input devices support boost.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/MicrophoneHardwa: <c val="ffffff">Mute OS Microphone:</c><n/>Toggles the OS microphone mute state.<n/><n/><c val="ff0000">Note: This will affect other applications and will remain in effect when StarCraft II is not running.</c>
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/MicrophoneTest: <c val="ffffff">Microphone Test:</c><n/>Toggle the microphone test. While enabled, all voice spoken through the microphone will play back through the selected voice output device.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/MicrophoneVolume: <c val="ffffff">Microphone Volume:</c><n/>Determines how loudly audio is recorded. Increase this if others have a hard time hearing you. Disabled if Auto setting is being used.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/Mode: <c val="ffffff">Voice Chat Mode:</c><n/>Determines how your microphone is activated. Voice Activated will automatically activate chat when you speak. Push-to-Talk requires you to hold a button while speaking.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/OutputDevice: <c val="ffffff">Output Device:</c><n/>Selects the speakers or headphones used to play back voice chat. Voice chat does not need to play through the same device as the game.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/PTTHotkey: <c val="ffffff">Push-to-Talk Key:</c><n/>Determines the key used to activate voice chat. Press the button then the key you want to use to change this value.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/PTTSound: <c val="ffffff">Push-to-Talk Sound:</c><n/>When enabled, a small chime will play when you press or release your Push-to-Talk key.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/Provider: <c val="ffffff">Provider:</c><n/>Selects the voice chat input/output provider.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/VoiceChat: <c val="ffffff">Enable Voice Chat:</c><n/>Enables the ability to listen or participate in voice chat during gameplay.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/VoiceChatParenta: <c val="ff0000">Voice Chat:</c><n/>This feature has been disabled by parental control.
GameStrings.UI/VoiceOptionsTooltips/VoiceToast: <c val="ffffff">Enable Voice Toasts:</c><n/>Enables the display of indicators which show who is currently speaking in voice chat.
